        {
            "_id": "X0RMAYFeESgrAaxL",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Fear the Chain",
            "sort": 700000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The dragoons attempt to [[/act demoralize]] all foes in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:15], comparing the result of a single Intimidation check to each target's Will DC. The squad doesn't take the penalty if they don't speak the same language as a target. It's possible for the dragoon squad to get a different degree of success for each target, and a target is temporarily immune to this ability only if the squad critically fails the check against them.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
